{{Use British English|date=August 2016}}
'''Samuel Gilburne''' (fl. 1605, d. after 1623) was an [[English Renaissance theatre|Elizabethan]] [[actor]] who is listed as one of the "Principall Actors" in the prefatory material of the [[First Folio]] of William Shakespeare's plays. Gilburne is named as a former apprentice to [[Augustine Phillips]], another member of Shakespeare's company, in Phillips' will dated 4 May 1605, in which Gilburne is bequeathed 40 shillings, Phillips's "mouse-colored" velvet hose, his black taffeta suit and white taffeta doublet, his purple cloak, his sword and dagger, and his bass [[viol]]. A copy of the First Folio held at the [[Folger Shakespeare Library]] has a signature thought to be Gilburne's.

